OL,3,CSussex hospices fears services will be
OL,4,Ccut if government funding fails
OL,6,FMore people would have to die in
OL,7,Fhospital rather than the comfort of
OL,8,Ftheir home or a hospice, if the
OL,9,Fgovernment doesn't provide new funding
OL,10,Ffor end-of-life care, according to the
OL,11,Fhead of a hospice group in Sussex.
OL,13,FThe Southern Hospice Group provides
OL,14,Fservices for more than 4000 people
OL,15,Facross Sussex and East Hampshire.
OL,17,FBut Stuart Palma, its chief executive,
OL,18,Fsaid these will have to be reduced
OL,19,Fwithout long-term funding.
