OL,3,CSussex hospices fears services will be
OL,4,Ccut if government funding fails
OL,6,FThey typically rely on a mixture of
OL,7,Fgovernment money and charity
OL,8,Ffundraising to provide their services.
OL,10,FLast year, Southern Hospice Group
OL,11,Fmerged three of its hospices - St
OL,12,FBarnabas in Worthing, the Martlets in
OL,13,FHove and Chestnut Tree House in
OL,14,FArundel - in an effort to save money.
OL,16,FIt cost #34m pounds to keep the three
OL,17,Fsites running in the most recent
OL,18,Ffinancial year. The majority of that
OL,19,Ffunding came from public donations
OL,20,Fwith around 7 million pounds provided
OL,21,Fby the government.
